body:
# Zod Validation

Validation is the core purpose of Zod. Define constraints, parse data, handle errors.

## Parsing Modes

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";

const schema = z.string().email();

// .parse() — throws ZodError on failure
try {
  const email = schema.parse(input);
} catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof z.ZodError) {
    console.error(e.issues);
  }
}

// .safeParse() — never throws, returns discriminated union
const result = schema.safeParse(input);
if (result.success) {
  result.data; // string (validated email)
} else {
  result.error; // ZodError
}

// Async variants (required if schema has async refinements/transforms)
const asyncResult = await schema.safeParseAsync(input);
```

## String Validators

```typescript
z.string().min(1)                  // min length
z.string().max(255)                // max length
z.string().length(10)              // exact length
z.string().email()                 // email format
z.string().url()                   // URL format
z.string().uuid()                  // UUID format
z.string().cuid()                  // CUID format
z.string().cuid2()                 // CUID2 format
z.string().ulid()                  // ULID format
z.string().regex(/^[A-Z]+$/)       // regex match
z.string().includes("needle")      // contains substring
z.string().startsWith("https://")  // prefix check
z.string().endsWith(".com")        // suffix check
z.string().datetime()              // ISO 8601 datetime
z.string().ip()                    // IPv4 or IPv6
z.string().trim()                  // trims whitespace (transform)
z.string().toLowerCase()           // lowercases (transform)
z.string().toUpperCase()           // uppercases (transform)
z.string().emoji()                 // emoji characters only
```

## Number Validators

```typescript
z.number().gt(0)            // > 0 (exclusive)
z.number().gte(0)           // >= 0 (inclusive) — alias: .min(0)
z.number().lt(100)          // < 100
z.number().lte(100)         // <= 100 — alias: .max(100)
z.number().int()            // integer only
z.number().positive()       // > 0
z.number().nonnegative()    // >= 0
z.number().negative()       // < 0
z.number().nonpositive()    // <= 0
z.number().multipleOf(5)    // divisible by 5 — alias: .step(5)
z.number().finite()         // not Infinity or -Infinity
z.number().safe()           // within Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER..MAX_SAFE_INTEGER
```

## Date Validators

```typescript
z.date().min(new Date("2020-01-01"))  // after date
z.date().max(new Date("2030-12-31"))  // before date
```

## Custom Refinements

```typescript
// .refine() — simple custom validation
const PasswordSchema = z.string()
  .min(8)
  .refine((val) => /[A-Z]/.test(val), {
    message: "Must contain at least one uppercase letter",
  })
  .refine((val) => /[0-9]/.test(val), {
    message: "Must contain at least one number",
  });

// .superRefine() — full control over error issues
const ConfirmPassword = z.object({
  password: z.string().min(8),
  confirm: z.string(),
}).superRefine((data, ctx) => {
  if (data.password !== data.confirm) {
    ctx.addIssue({
      code: z.ZodIssueCode.custom,
      message: "Passwords don't match",
      path: ["confirm"],
    });
  }
});

// Async refinements
const UniqueEmail = z.string().email().refine(
  async (email) => {
    const exists = await checkEmailExists(email);
    return !exists;
  },
  { message: "Email already in use" }
);
// Must use .parseAsync() or .safeParseAsync() with async refinements
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
const UserSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, "Name is required"),
  email: z.string().email("Invalid email"),
  age: z.number({ invalid_type_error: "Age must be a number" })
    .int("Age must be a whole number")
    .positive("Age must be positive"),
});

const result = UserSchema.safeParse(input);
if (!result.success) {
  // .issues — array of ZodIssue objects
  result.error.issues;
  // [{ code: "too_small", minimum: 1, path: ["name"], message: "Name is required" }]

  // .flatten() — flat object with fieldErrors and formErrors
  result.error.flatten();
  // { formErrors: [], fieldErrors: { name: ["Name is required"], email: ["Invalid email"] } }

  // .format() — nested object matching schema shape
  result.error.format();
  // { name: { _errors: ["Name is required"] }, email: { _errors: ["Invalid email"] } }
}
```

## Custom Error Messages

```typescript
// Inline on validators
z.string().min(1, "Required")
z.string().min(1, { message: "Required" })
z.number().max(100, "Too large")

// On the base type
z.string({ required_error: "Name is required", invalid_type_error: "Must be a string" })
z.number({ invalid_type_error: "Expected a number" })

// Global error map
z.setErrorMap((issue, ctx) => {
  if (issue.code === z.ZodIssueCode.too_small) {
    return { message: `Minimum length is ${issue.minimum}` };
  }
  return { message: ctx.defaultError };
});
```

## ZodError Issue Types

Common issue codes: `invalid_type`, `invalid_literal`, `custom`, `invalid_union`, `invalid_union_discriminator`, `invalid_enum_value`, `unrecognized_keys`, `invalid_arguments`, `invalid_return_type`, `invalid_date`, `invalid_string`, `too_small`, `too_big`, `invalid_intersection_types`, `not_multiple_of`, `not_finite`.
